article.linkText: Gordon scores 18 to help Iona defeat Harvard 69-60
article.story: BOSTON -- — Greg Gordon had 18 points in Iona's 69-60 win against Harvard on Saturday. Gordon also had 12 rebounds for the Gaels (6-7). Idan Tretout scored 15 points while going 5 of 13 from the floor, including 1 for 6 from 3-point range, and 4 for 7 from the line, and added five rebounds. Jeremiah Quigley shot 5 of 12 from the field and 4 for 6 from the line to finish with 15 points. Chisom Okpara led the way for the Crimson (8-4) with 15 points and eight rebounds. Harvard also got 12 points from Louis Lesmond. In addition, Thomas Batties II finished with 11 points, 10 rebounds and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
